refactor(deskwork): extract @deskwork/core npm package

First commit toward severing the plugin from in-tree code. Per the plan
in /Users/orion/.claude/plans/i-would-like-to-wiggly-hennessy.md, the
target is a thin SKILL-only plugin pointing at npm-published packages
(@deskwork/cli, @deskwork/studio later) so:
  - Headless skills don't carry studio weight
  - Studio doesn't depend on Astro
  - Plugin updates decouple from npm-package updates

This commit moves the lib code out of the plugin tree into its own
workspace package. Behavior unchanged. The bin/ scripts and
integration tests now resolve `@deskwork/core/<subpath>` through the
npm-workspace symlink instead of relative `../lib/X.ts` imports.

Changes:
- Add packages/core/ workspace with src/, test/, package.json, tsconfig,
  vitest config. Subpath exports cover all internal modules.
- Move plugins/deskwork/lib/* → packages/core/src/* (git mv preserves
  history)
- Move 9 lib tests → packages/core/test/* with `../src/X.ts` imports
- Update plugins/deskwork/package.json: drop yaml/unified/remark/
  rehype-stringify (now @deskwork/core deps); declare @deskwork/core: *
- Update plugins/deskwork/bin/* and 3 integration tests to import from
  @deskwork/core/<subpath>
- Update root package.json workspaces: ["packages/*", "plugins/*"]
- Update review-lifecycle-integration.test.ts inline tsx scripts to
  use @deskwork/core/review/pipeline + @deskwork/core/config (no more
  pluginRoot/lib/...)

Verified:
- 126/126 @deskwork/core tests pass
- 27/27 @deskwork/plugin tests pass (3 integration files spawning real
  bin scripts via tsx)
- npm --workspaces run typecheck clean
- claude plugin validate plugins/deskwork passes
- claude --plugin-dir lists all 12 skills

Next commits per the plan: extract @deskwork/cli (bin/ → packages/cli/),
build @deskwork/studio (Hono server + UI), add deskwork-studio plugin
shell.
